oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This image shows an example of the information included on the back of photographs in the Photographs of W. L. Clement Collection. Mr. Clement, District Conservationist for Cannon County, provided detailed notes on the content of of each image. The information appears to be a mimeograph copy of a typewritten original. Each photograph was individually typed in a typewriter.; One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Photographs of W.L. Clement, U.S. Soil Conservation Service;
